1
00:00:30,166 --> 00:00:34,136
(Azure Spring)

2
00:00:34,137 --> 00:00:36,905
(All characters, places, events, etc. depicted are fictional.)

3
00:00:36,906 --> 00:00:39,075
(Children and animals were filmed under strict guidelines.)

4
00:00:50,553 --> 00:00:55,025
(The 7th Tongyeong Open Water Swimming Competition)

5
00:00:58,495 --> 00:01:00,964
(Tongyeong, Bijin-do, Maemul-do)

6
00:01:02,299 --> 00:01:04,701
What can I do to help him?

7
00:01:15,578 --> 00:01:16,879
(Enjoy the clear sea at Haedam-do, Tongyeong)

8
00:01:16,880 --> 00:01:18,647
(The 7th Tongyeong Open Water Swimming Competition)

9
00:01:18,648 --> 00:01:19,716
Open water swimming?

10
00:01:30,527 --> 00:01:36,533
(Episode 6: Azure Spring)

11
00:01:37,067 --> 00:01:40,402
(7th Tongyeong Open Water Swimming Competition)

12
00:01:40,403 --> 00:01:41,571
Let's compete in a swim meet.

13
00:01:45,575 --> 00:01:46,977
What are you suddenly talking about?

14
00:01:48,411 --> 00:01:50,379
I came to say that to you,

15
00:01:50,380 --> 00:01:51,715
and now that I have, I'm leaving.

16
00:01:52,315 --> 00:01:54,417
How long will you stay underwater?

17
00:01:56,252 --> 00:01:58,355
You told me I had to let things go and come back up...

18
00:02:00,490 --> 00:02:01,725
to live.

19
00:02:13,269 --> 00:02:14,571
I'll teach you...

20
00:02:16,573 --> 00:02:17,774
how to float on water.

21
00:02:26,016 --> 00:02:27,017
Come on.

22
00:02:28,118 --> 00:02:29,252
Hurry up.

23
00:02:34,090 --> 00:02:35,158
Remember the rules?

24
00:02:35,558 --> 00:02:37,259
You get the inner room, and I get the master bedroom.

25
00:02:37,260 --> 00:02:39,261
We share the kitchen and restroom, but we must wash our own dishes.

26
00:02:39,262 --> 00:02:40,897
Why are you doing this to me?

27
00:02:42,532 --> 00:02:43,766
It's just...

28
00:02:43,767 --> 00:02:46,936
kind of scary to see a tanned guy like you with a frown.

29
00:02:50,307 --> 00:02:52,208
I want to make you smile.

30
00:03:01,084 --> 00:03:03,420
Gosh, I'm starving. Why don't we...

31
00:03:03,954 --> 00:03:05,055
eat something first?

32
00:03:14,097 --> 00:03:17,167
Food must be frozen to preserve it longer.

33
00:03:50,667 --> 00:03:52,534
But if you freeze it for too long,

34
00:03:52,535 --> 00:03:54,104
thawing becomes difficult.

35
00:04:47,357 --> 00:04:49,492
What are you waiting for? Come on.

36
00:05:15,251 --> 00:05:17,253
And now, high-five!

37
00:05:18,388 --> 00:05:19,856
The same goes for people's hearts.

38
00:05:20,523 --> 00:05:22,058
A heart left alone for a long time...

39
00:05:22,892 --> 00:05:24,461
doesn't thaw too easily.

40
00:05:43,280 --> 00:05:45,915
That's when you need a special prescription.

41
00:06:33,763 --> 00:06:34,764
Ta-da.

42
00:06:35,632 --> 00:06:37,534
Why don't you take a bite?

43
00:06:42,005 --> 00:06:44,107
Thank you for the food.

44
00:07:05,462 --> 00:07:06,630
Who could've made this?

45
00:07:07,163 --> 00:07:08,665
It's so good!

46
00:07:18,008 --> 00:07:19,476
Here, try this one, too.

47
00:07:34,224 --> 00:07:35,925
- Is it good? - Yes.

48
00:07:37,661 --> 00:07:39,095
Come on. Eat up.

49
00:07:56,246 --> 00:07:57,414
That was delicious.

50
00:08:09,292 --> 00:08:12,295
Since when did you like cats?

51
00:08:17,767 --> 00:08:19,135
I don't particularly like them.

52
00:08:20,870 --> 00:08:22,472
Ever since I came to this island,

53
00:08:23,073 --> 00:08:25,942
I noticed them lingering around, so I've simply been feeding it.

54
00:08:28,912 --> 00:08:33,216
People usually call that liking something.

55
00:08:34,851 --> 00:08:37,320
- Is that so? - Yes.

56
00:08:38,254 --> 00:08:40,489
Who would feed anyone that they hate?

57
00:08:40,490 --> 00:08:41,925
It takes affection.

58
00:08:48,832 --> 00:08:50,233
But that doesn't necessarily mean...

59
00:08:50,734 --> 00:08:53,103
that I like you.

60
00:08:57,240 --> 00:08:58,241
I know.

61
00:08:59,276 --> 00:09:00,910
You wouldn't like a guy like me.

62
00:09:03,013 --> 00:09:04,414
What's so bad about you?

63
00:09:05,048 --> 00:09:08,151
You're perfectly healthy, and you make a living for yourself.

64
00:09:08,952 --> 00:09:09,953
That's enough.

65
00:09:13,490 --> 00:09:15,292
I'm an ex-convict.

66
00:09:17,661 --> 00:09:19,362
I'm aware of that.

67
00:09:27,037 --> 00:09:28,104
I ruined...

68
00:09:30,473 --> 00:09:32,309
two people's lives.

69
00:09:37,814 --> 00:09:40,717
I'm aware of that, too.

70
00:09:43,887 --> 00:09:45,822
That stalker of yours...

71
00:09:47,223 --> 00:09:48,858
came to my place in Seoul.

72
00:09:52,262 --> 00:09:53,263
He asked me...

73
00:09:54,564 --> 00:09:56,032
to save you.

74
00:09:58,001 --> 00:10:00,070
He said you smiled when you were with me.

75
00:10:18,521 --> 00:10:20,156
He was a junior soldier I cared about.

76
00:10:23,760 --> 00:10:27,864
He was soft-hearted, so he wasn't fit to serve in the army.

77
00:10:33,570 --> 00:10:34,771
Like how it always is,

78
00:10:36,573 --> 00:10:38,341
the weak became prey.

79
00:10:41,645 --> 00:10:42,912
He began to get bullied.

80
00:10:46,850 --> 00:10:48,918
And I couldn't tolerate it at that moment.

81
00:10:52,722 --> 00:10:54,090
One died,

82
00:10:56,693 --> 00:10:57,894
and the other...

83
00:11:00,730 --> 00:11:02,432
lives as if he were dead.

84
00:11:09,706 --> 00:11:11,074
At times, I begin to wonder,

85
00:11:16,813 --> 00:11:17,948
"What if..."

86
00:11:20,216 --> 00:11:21,584
"I did not stop him back then?"

87
00:11:26,756 --> 00:11:28,325
It could've ended...

88
00:11:31,995 --> 00:11:34,998
as a simple beating with a broken bone,

89
00:11:37,267 --> 00:11:39,936
and it would've been over.

90
00:11:48,378 --> 00:11:49,379
Then...

91
00:11:53,984 --> 00:11:55,785
that jerk, Nam Sang Ho, would've lived,

92
00:12:02,292 --> 00:12:04,160
and Jae Hui would've been fine, too.

93
00:12:18,341 --> 00:12:19,342
No.

94
00:12:23,280 --> 00:12:25,515
It wouldn't have ended that easily.

95
00:12:28,251 --> 00:12:30,320
The situation would've escalated,

96
00:12:33,556 --> 00:12:34,824
so in the end,

97
00:12:38,495 --> 00:12:39,963
it would've ended in the same way.

98
00:12:44,401 --> 00:12:46,169
You did the right thing.

99
00:12:49,506 --> 00:12:50,974
Everything that happened after that...

100
00:12:54,577 --> 00:12:55,912
is just an accident.

101
00:13:06,156 --> 00:13:07,657
I'm saying...

102
00:13:10,660 --> 00:13:11,728
it wasn't your fault.

103
00:13:55,472 --> 00:13:56,940
I became quite nosy,

104
00:13:57,774 --> 00:13:58,942
thanks to this guy.

105
00:14:09,219 --> 00:14:12,588
Shouldn't the newcomer hand out rice cakes?

106
00:14:12,589 --> 00:14:13,657
Why am I bringing this?

107
00:14:14,491 --> 00:14:16,793
Hey, An Na. My dad told me to give you some rice cake.

108
00:14:23,233 --> 00:14:24,501
Su Jeong?

109
00:14:24,934 --> 00:14:27,404
Seo An Na, you...

110
00:14:35,578 --> 00:14:39,349
Su Jeong, it's not like what it seems.

111
00:14:40,317 --> 00:14:42,751
We ate dinner and talked, then got too exhausted...

112
00:14:42,752 --> 00:14:44,487
How can you do this to me?

113
00:14:58,835 --> 00:14:59,836
Hey!

114
00:15:07,510 --> 00:15:09,478
Hey, look at this.

115
00:15:09,479 --> 00:15:11,113
(7th Tongyeong Open Water Swimming Competition)

116
00:15:11,114 --> 00:15:12,949
We were really talking about the swim meet.

117
00:15:14,651 --> 00:15:16,318
She's right. The swim meet.

118
00:15:16,319 --> 00:15:18,355
She suggested that we compete in this.

119
00:15:19,189 --> 00:15:21,858
You two returned to Parang-ri at the same time on the same day.

120
00:15:22,392 --> 00:15:24,561
Are you saying you talked about the swim meet all night?

121
00:15:25,996 --> 00:15:27,163
But why?

122
00:15:27,530 --> 00:15:30,033
I'm going to settle down here,

123
00:15:30,800 --> 00:15:32,802
so I need to make a living for myself.

124
00:15:33,336 --> 00:15:35,839
I wanted to win the cash prize.

125
00:15:36,172 --> 00:15:37,374
Fine, that's your story.

126
00:15:38,408 --> 00:15:40,844
Why are you competing, Duk Hyun?

127
00:15:41,011 --> 00:15:42,178
I'm not...

128
00:15:44,014 --> 00:15:46,883
I am competing with An Na. Yes.

129
00:15:51,988 --> 00:15:53,256
Then I want to do it, too.

130
00:15:53,923 --> 00:15:56,626
I can't let you two train alone, like you did when harvesting seafood.

131
00:15:58,762 --> 00:16:00,664
Sure. Okay.

132
00:16:01,231 --> 00:16:04,166
You're more than welcome. Yes.

133
00:16:04,167 --> 00:16:05,335
Then I'm in, too.

134
00:16:06,936 --> 00:16:10,507
Why is that new guy back in this backwater village?

135
00:16:11,041 --> 00:16:14,544
That guy paid a dear friend's hospital bill in full.

136
00:16:15,111 --> 00:16:17,247
I want to win the cash prize and pay for half of it.

137
00:16:18,214 --> 00:16:20,050
- Will you let me join? - Yes.

138
00:16:20,884 --> 00:16:21,952
No!

139
00:16:24,521 --> 00:16:25,754
I am...

140
00:16:25,755 --> 00:16:27,290
the Piranha of the Black Snake Unit.

141
00:16:27,691 --> 00:16:29,025
I don't know about everything else,

142
00:16:29,392 --> 00:16:30,961
but I do know I can swim.

143
00:16:37,901 --> 00:16:39,602
The chance of us winning just dropped.

144
00:16:47,944 --> 00:16:49,545
(7th Tongyeong Open Water Swimming Competition)

145
00:16:49,546 --> 00:16:53,048
(Saturday, September 6th, 2025, Tongyeong Haedamdo Beach)

146
00:16:53,049 --> 00:16:55,918
(7th Tongyeong Open Water Swimming Competition)

147
00:16:55,919 --> 00:16:57,886
- Let's go. - It's so pretty. Let's go.

148
00:16:57,887 --> 00:16:59,889
(Sign-Up Form, Seo An Na, 5-1 Parang-ri-gil)

149
00:17:08,898 --> 00:17:10,132
(Name: Yoon Duk Hyun)

150
00:17:10,133 --> 00:17:11,134
(Address)

151
00:17:22,579 --> 00:17:23,980
(Address: 5-1 Parang-ri-gil)

152
00:17:33,823 --> 00:17:36,893
(T-Shirt Size: XL, Signature)

153
00:17:45,035 --> 00:17:46,169
So...

154
00:17:47,637 --> 00:17:51,308
why in the world are you trying to teach me how to swim?

155
00:17:54,978 --> 00:17:56,880
If you ask why it had to be swimming...

156
00:18:03,019 --> 00:18:06,189
All right. Think of the tissue paper as water.

157
00:18:06,823 --> 00:18:09,191
Faster! Do not drop it.

158
00:18:09,192 --> 00:18:11,428
- Pick it up. - It was about the time he'd spend learning.

159
00:18:12,128 --> 00:18:13,964
- I wanted to gift him that moment. - Faster!

160
00:18:14,965 --> 00:18:16,232
- One, two! - One, two!

161
00:18:16,800 --> 00:18:18,234
- One, two! - One, two!

162
00:18:18,735 --> 00:18:19,970
One, two!

163
00:18:20,670 --> 00:18:21,671
One, two!

164
00:18:22,572 --> 00:18:25,342
One, two! Do not drop your shoulders!

165
00:18:27,243 --> 00:18:28,311
One, two!

166
00:18:30,046 --> 00:18:32,015
Just like when he taught me how to harvest seafood.

167
00:18:33,083 --> 00:18:34,084
Good job!

168
00:18:34,317 --> 00:18:35,685
In that moment,

169
00:18:36,720 --> 00:18:38,822
- nothing else was on my mind. - Faster!

170
00:18:44,761 --> 00:18:47,931
I wanted to return that peace to him.

171
00:18:57,007 --> 00:18:59,175
Gosh, I'm starving.

172
00:18:59,542 --> 00:19:02,278
Since we spent time in the water, why don't we eat hot soup?

173
00:19:02,279 --> 00:19:04,114
Your face will get bloated if you have soup at night.

174
00:19:04,247 --> 00:19:06,715
Then what do you eat at night, new guy?

175
00:19:06,716 --> 00:19:09,319
- Me? Salad. - Right. Sure.

176
00:19:10,420 --> 00:19:13,355
Duk Hyun, what do you want to eat?

177
00:19:13,356 --> 00:19:15,125
Anything is fine with me.

178
00:19:16,459 --> 00:19:17,794
So boring.

179
00:19:18,895 --> 00:19:20,096
Okay, I got it.

180
00:19:20,864 --> 00:19:22,799
Hot soup, salad,

181
00:19:23,166 --> 00:19:24,200
and anything.

182
00:19:24,567 --> 00:19:26,336
Let's eat something we'll all be pleased with.

183
00:19:59,970 --> 00:20:01,103
Oh, gosh.

184
00:20:01,104 --> 00:20:04,140
Manila clams are salty, so our faces will definitely get puffy.

185
00:20:07,611 --> 00:20:08,678
Darn it.

186
00:21:05,502 --> 00:21:06,703
Come on.

187
00:21:07,170 --> 00:21:09,706
Seasoned veggies aren't filling enough.

188
00:21:12,309 --> 00:21:13,310
Scoot over.

189
00:21:14,210 --> 00:21:15,478
You're so slow.

190
00:21:19,883 --> 00:21:21,017
You know how to do that?

191
00:21:21,584 --> 00:21:23,987
I was the Frying Pan of the Black Snake Unit.

192
00:21:26,022 --> 00:21:27,023
Not bad.

193
00:22:05,929 --> 00:22:06,930
Here.

194
00:22:08,131 --> 00:22:09,299
Goodness, no way.

195
00:22:10,467 --> 00:22:11,468
What is this?

196
00:22:12,702 --> 00:22:13,703
Is it dog food?

197
00:22:14,137 --> 00:22:15,739
How dare you? "Dog food"?

198
00:22:16,072 --> 00:22:17,374
It's mixed wild green rice.

199
00:22:17,774 --> 00:22:20,644
You're right. Mixed wild green rice is way better than salad.

200
00:22:24,314 --> 00:22:26,816
You just threw in everything you had at home.

201
00:22:27,917 --> 00:22:29,252
Why don't we talk after you try it?

202
00:22:36,092 --> 00:22:38,394
Now, mix. Go!

203
00:22:38,395 --> 00:22:39,396
Go!

204
00:22:44,334 --> 00:22:45,335
Go.

205
00:22:49,239 --> 00:22:51,074
If we continue to learn and mingle together,

206
00:22:52,475 --> 00:22:53,710
the dishes,

207
00:22:55,078 --> 00:22:56,079
the people,

208
00:22:57,814 --> 00:22:58,915
and even wounds...

209
00:23:00,250 --> 00:23:02,953
may start to soften and fade.

210
00:23:08,491 --> 00:23:10,360
It's so good. Hurry up and try it.

211
00:23:11,127 --> 00:23:14,197
It may even get a little better.

212
00:23:15,465 --> 00:23:17,467
Open up, Duk Hyun.

213
00:23:17,667 --> 00:23:18,668
Or not.

214
00:23:28,278 --> 00:23:30,013
Hurry up and try it. It's really good.

215
00:24:02,846 --> 00:24:04,347
It's not so bad for dog food.

216
00:24:05,682 --> 00:24:07,017
Stop calling it dog food.

217
00:24:07,584 --> 00:24:09,152
You liked it, so you can't call it that!

218
00:24:17,527 --> 00:24:18,528
Look.

219
00:24:19,262 --> 00:24:20,563
It's good, though.

220
00:24:25,335 --> 00:24:26,436
Seo An Na.

221
00:24:27,203 --> 00:24:30,105
How dare you dump me and date a guy like that?

222
00:24:30,106 --> 00:24:31,374
That's basically it.

223
00:24:37,781 --> 00:24:40,083
Yoon Duk Hyun!

224
00:24:45,622 --> 00:24:46,623
Yoon Duk Hyun!

225
00:24:47,891 --> 00:24:48,892
Come on out!

226
00:24:49,426 --> 00:24:50,760
Are you here, Yoon Duk Hyun?

227
00:24:58,268 --> 00:25:00,970
Chief, what brings you here?

228
00:25:00,971 --> 00:25:02,339
Baek Su Jeong, you brat.

229
00:25:02,806 --> 00:25:05,342
Why did you sleep here instead of your own home?

230
00:25:06,443 --> 00:25:07,743
Come on, Dad.

231
00:25:07,744 --> 00:25:09,745
I'm old enough, so don't nag at me for spending the night out...

232
00:25:09,746 --> 00:25:11,046
on this tiny little island.

233
00:25:11,047 --> 00:25:12,749
Well, no. It's not that.

234
00:25:13,383 --> 00:25:14,784
Doesn't Yoon Duk Hyun live here?

235
00:25:15,685 --> 00:25:17,820
What about him?

236
00:25:17,821 --> 00:25:19,422
It's not like he just moved in.

237
00:25:19,689 --> 00:25:20,690
That kid is...

238
00:25:22,425 --> 00:25:23,426
Look.

239
00:25:24,427 --> 00:25:26,463
- There he is. - What's going on?

240
00:25:27,030 --> 00:25:29,966
I thought you had left the island. Why did you return?

241
00:25:31,267 --> 00:25:34,137
Did I cause an inconvenience with my return?

242
00:25:34,471 --> 00:25:35,538
Of course, you have!

243
00:25:36,806 --> 00:25:39,009
We all know who you are now.

244
00:25:40,777 --> 00:25:42,012
Dad.

245
00:25:42,912 --> 00:25:44,214
What do you mean?

246
00:25:45,782 --> 00:25:46,950
Who is he?

247
00:25:50,453 --> 00:25:53,189
That he's a murderer who killed a person.

248
00:25:54,858 --> 00:25:55,892
Cha Jae Hun.

249
00:25:57,627 --> 00:26:00,130
An Na, you... Gosh.

250
00:26:01,031 --> 00:26:04,534
Wait, have you been hitting it off with him, knowing who he is?

251
00:26:05,268 --> 00:26:07,771
An Na, what's he talking about?

252
00:26:08,972 --> 00:26:12,175
Did Duk Hyun kill a person?

253
00:26:13,343 --> 00:26:16,579
One died, and the other is a vegetable.

254
00:26:17,113 --> 00:26:18,715
Technically, he killed two people.

255
00:26:22,886 --> 00:26:24,387
Excuse me, Chief.

256
00:26:24,821 --> 00:26:28,023
How can you let a guy like that stay in this peaceful village?

257
00:26:28,024 --> 00:26:29,793
Jae Hun, how dare you?

258
00:26:47,777 --> 00:26:48,778
I'm sorry.

259
00:26:50,547 --> 00:26:51,982
I couldn't bring myself to tell you.

260
00:26:53,817 --> 00:26:54,818
I will leave the island...

261
00:26:55,652 --> 00:26:56,753
within the day.

262
00:26:58,088 --> 00:26:59,089
Yes!

263
00:27:00,056 --> 00:27:01,725
You should've said that in the first place.

264
00:27:07,731 --> 00:27:09,065
You should've told us...

265
00:27:10,600 --> 00:27:13,103
when you got here three years ago.

266
00:27:25,615 --> 00:27:26,916
Keeping that all to yourself...

267
00:27:28,485 --> 00:27:29,619
must've been tough.

268
00:27:36,359 --> 00:27:37,360
I bet.

269
00:27:38,128 --> 00:27:40,263
We've known you for a long time.

270
00:27:40,597 --> 00:27:43,433
He lived all three years just harvesting seafood.

271
00:27:45,001 --> 00:27:47,170
We all know how to use the Internet.

272
00:27:47,804 --> 00:27:50,440
We already looked into the details of the incident.

273
00:27:50,974 --> 00:27:53,376
- You went through a lot. - It must've been tough.

274
00:27:56,646 --> 00:27:59,049
What are these old people saying?

275
00:27:59,950 --> 00:28:02,252
This punk killed a person!

276
00:28:04,854 --> 00:28:05,989
Darn it.

277
00:28:07,157 --> 00:28:08,525
Hey, An Na. Come on out.

278
00:28:09,926 --> 00:28:10,961
- An Na! - Hey!

279
00:28:14,831 --> 00:28:15,832
Let go.

280
00:28:16,132 --> 00:28:17,133
Didn't you hear me?

281
00:28:18,134 --> 00:28:21,104
- I'm a former swimmer. - Is that so?

282
00:28:22,472 --> 00:28:23,807
- I was a judo wrestler. - What?

283
00:28:36,152 --> 00:28:37,486
Only until elementary school.

284
00:28:37,487 --> 00:28:39,623
- My goodness. - You're a strong one!

285
00:28:40,190 --> 00:28:41,191
- Goodness. - Good one.

286
00:28:41,591 --> 00:28:44,861
Anyway, now that you're back,

287
00:28:45,161 --> 00:28:47,664
live a good life here without thinking of running away.

288
00:28:48,031 --> 00:28:50,634
- Got it? - He's right.

289
00:28:51,201 --> 00:28:55,138
A young man like you is rare in this small island village.

290
00:28:55,939 --> 00:28:58,208
- Got it? - That's right!

291
00:28:58,508 --> 00:29:00,277
- There's nothing much to life. - That's true.

292
00:29:00,810 --> 00:29:04,313
Life is about learning how to coexist with others.

293
00:29:04,314 --> 00:29:05,548
He's right.

294
00:29:06,983 --> 00:29:08,218
- Where's the rice cake? - Here.

295
00:29:09,185 --> 00:29:11,253
Where's the rice cake? Bring it here.

296
00:29:11,254 --> 00:29:12,255
Have some rice cake.

297
00:29:12,889 --> 00:29:14,591
Once you've moved to a new place,

298
00:29:14,958 --> 00:29:17,593
it's customary to give out steamed rice cakes.

299
00:29:17,594 --> 00:29:19,462
- He's right. - Open up.

300
00:29:19,729 --> 00:29:21,263
I already gave him some.

301
00:29:21,264 --> 00:29:23,133
That was for An Na.

302
00:29:24,634 --> 00:29:25,969
All of you, open up.

303
00:29:27,971 --> 00:29:28,972
Have some.

304
00:29:30,140 --> 00:29:31,141
Open up.

305
00:29:33,743 --> 00:29:35,345
It's nice to see you eat well.

306
00:29:37,380 --> 00:29:40,817
- Do you want some? - Goodness. Leave them for the kids.

307
00:29:43,353 --> 00:29:44,688
Just as the elders said,

308
00:29:45,455 --> 00:29:48,725
I guess there really isn't much to life.

309
00:29:49,492 --> 00:29:52,094
It's customary to give out rice cakes to the elders...

310
00:29:52,095 --> 00:29:53,496
and visit them when you move in.

311
00:29:55,198 --> 00:29:58,467
Goodness. Stop crying.

312
00:29:58,468 --> 00:30:01,905
You're a grown man. Don't cry. It's all right.

313
00:30:02,539 --> 00:30:04,874
We understand. Goodness.

314
00:30:05,709 --> 00:30:08,745
- Don't cry. - There, there. I'm glad you're here.

315
00:30:10,213 --> 00:30:11,480
Look at this guy.

316
00:30:11,481 --> 00:30:14,584
- Even bottled-up feelings and tangled emotions... - Oh, no. Come on now.

317
00:30:15,552 --> 00:30:19,189
all seem to melt away with a bite of steamed rice cake.

318
00:30:33,570 --> 00:30:35,639
Hey, that's pretty far.

319
00:30:36,640 --> 00:30:37,641
I'm out.

320
00:30:38,775 --> 00:30:41,211
No one told me about Duk Hyun,

321
00:30:41,611 --> 00:30:42,712
so I'm pouting.

322
00:30:43,146 --> 00:30:45,649
Cut it out. We're starting the open-water training from today.

323
00:30:46,116 --> 00:30:48,652
This is the starting point, and the buoy is the turning point.

324
00:30:49,486 --> 00:30:51,221
Dinner's on the loser.

325
00:30:51,621 --> 00:30:52,622
What do you say?

326
00:30:53,323 --> 00:30:54,424
Go!

327
00:30:54,758 --> 00:30:58,661
Hey! It'll cost a fortune to feed four people!

328
00:30:58,662 --> 00:30:59,896
Let's go!

329
00:31:01,264 --> 00:31:02,599
Hey, it's raining.

330
00:31:02,932 --> 00:31:04,333
- What? - Darn it.

331
00:31:04,334 --> 00:31:06,936
- It's raining. - Let's go home.

332
00:31:27,624 --> 00:31:28,792
- Duk Hyun. - Let's go home.

333
00:31:29,392 --> 00:31:31,261
- Come on. - Wait for me!

334
00:31:35,465 --> 00:31:36,466
Hurry.

335
00:31:37,567 --> 00:31:38,702
Jeez.

336
00:31:42,505 --> 00:31:43,740
Hand it over quickly.

337
00:31:46,743 --> 00:31:48,011
Say pretty please.

338
00:31:49,145 --> 00:31:50,146
Darn it.

339
00:31:51,481 --> 00:31:52,949
I'll give it to you.

340
00:31:54,618 --> 00:31:55,819
You're too slow!

341
00:31:57,153 --> 00:31:59,356
I can't do this!

342
00:32:02,826 --> 00:32:05,628
- Hey, don't drop it. - I can't do it!

343
00:32:05,629 --> 00:32:07,297
- I'm not doing this! - Hey!

344
00:32:12,869 --> 00:32:13,970
Come on!

345
00:32:19,743 --> 00:32:22,578
Hello, I signed up for the open-water competition.

346
00:32:22,579 --> 00:32:24,681
By any chance, will it be cancelled tomorrow?

347
00:32:25,148 --> 00:32:27,150
We'll know for sure when tomorrow comes.

348
00:32:27,751 --> 00:32:30,085
But tomorrow is the competition.

349
00:32:30,086 --> 00:32:32,054
The typhoon is moving fast,

350
00:32:32,055 --> 00:32:35,124
so the forecast said we might move out of its path soon.

351
00:32:35,125 --> 00:32:37,260
I see. All right.

352
00:32:39,095 --> 00:32:42,999
No matter how hard we try, we can never predict what's ahead.

353
00:32:50,040 --> 00:32:51,074
All we can do is...

354
00:32:51,775 --> 00:32:53,743
just live the life we're given.

355
00:33:03,753 --> 00:33:05,921
(Tongyeong Open Water Swimming Competition)

356
00:33:05,922 --> 00:33:07,724
(Congratulations on finishing the race.)

357
00:33:17,267 --> 00:33:18,702
With all these set up,

358
00:33:19,269 --> 00:33:21,972
I guess the competition will carry on as planned, right?

359
00:33:22,339 --> 00:33:23,940
The weather cleared up, too.

360
00:33:24,608 --> 00:33:27,310
- I'm sure it'll happen. - No, I don't think so.

361
00:33:27,711 --> 00:33:29,479
We have an announcement.

362
00:33:29,579 --> 00:33:32,114
The open-water swimming competition scheduled for today...

363
00:33:32,115 --> 00:33:34,083
has been cancelled...

364
00:33:34,084 --> 00:33:37,854
due to safety concerns caused by strong currents in the high seas.

365
00:33:38,154 --> 00:33:40,889
The entry fee will be fully refunded.

366
00:33:40,890 --> 00:33:45,095
We thank you once again for coming out today.

367
00:33:45,695 --> 00:33:47,197
Yes! I got it right!

368
00:33:47,564 --> 00:33:48,898
Why are you happy about that?

369
00:33:49,299 --> 00:33:50,967
We trained so hard!

370
00:33:52,002 --> 00:33:54,404
What now, Duk Hyun?

371
00:33:54,938 --> 00:33:57,339
We can't help it. Let's go back.

372
00:33:57,340 --> 00:33:58,341
No.

373
00:33:59,109 --> 00:34:01,678
We came all the way here, so it's a huge bummer.

374
00:34:02,846 --> 00:34:04,314
Let's do the competition...

375
00:34:05,649 --> 00:34:06,916
- on our own. - What?

376
00:34:07,851 --> 00:34:08,852
On our own?

377
00:34:09,419 --> 00:34:12,921
We have the participants, the swimsuits, and the sea.

378
00:34:12,922 --> 00:34:15,258
- Why not? - They said it was dangerous.

379
00:34:15,692 --> 00:34:17,460
We'll only go out to the safe area.

380
00:34:18,361 --> 00:34:19,429
How about up to that buoy?

381
00:34:20,096 --> 00:34:22,465
To that buoy?

382
00:34:25,035 --> 00:34:26,436
All right, now.

383
00:34:27,170 --> 00:34:31,875
Let us begin the first Parang-ri Swimming Competition!

384
00:34:32,242 --> 00:34:34,844
The loser has to do the dishes for a month.

385
00:34:34,945 --> 00:34:36,913
Ready, go!

386
00:34:37,213 --> 00:34:40,984
Jeez, she's being so childish again.

387
00:34:44,387 --> 00:34:46,890
But I won't lose against you... Hey!

388
00:34:47,290 --> 00:34:50,360
Hey, wait! This isn't fair!

389
00:35:30,433 --> 00:35:32,902
Just like the weather at sea,

390
00:35:33,370 --> 00:35:35,038
life is unpredictable.

391
00:35:38,441 --> 00:35:41,278
Maybe that's why we just have to go with the flow,

392
00:35:41,711 --> 00:35:43,580
like we're being swept away by the waves.

393
00:35:47,384 --> 00:35:50,453
But it's okay to live like that.

394
00:35:56,693 --> 00:35:58,361
Just do what you can,

395
00:35:59,763 --> 00:36:02,299
as much as you can, and live on.

396
00:36:27,457 --> 00:36:29,225
Youth isn't momentary,

397
00:36:29,960 --> 00:36:31,061
but lasts a lifetime.

398
00:36:33,330 --> 00:36:37,133
Because for us, today will always be spring and azure.

399
00:36:44,240 --> 00:36:45,675
- May it last a long time. - May it last a long time.

400
00:36:46,376 --> 00:36:48,278
- Azure spring. - Azure spring.

401
00:36:50,580 --> 00:36:56,586
(Azure Spring)

402
00:37:09,366 --> 00:37:10,600
Come here! Quickly!

403
00:37:12,669 --> 00:37:14,704
- Come on! - Hurry up, man.

404
00:37:15,338 --> 00:37:16,572
- The timer's about to go off. - Where?

405
00:37:16,573 --> 00:37:17,841
One, two!

406
00:37:55,478 --> 00:38:01,351
(Thank you for watching Azure Spring)
